Package main.model.camp

Class Camp

java.lang.Object
main.model.camp.Camp
All Implemented Interfaces:
Displayable, Model, Mappable
public class Camp extends Object implements Model, Displayable
The Camp class represents a camp object with various attributes. It implements the Model and Displayable interfaces.

  • Constructor Details

    • Camp

      public Camp(String campID, String campName, String dates, String registrationClosingDate, Faculty openTo, String location, int filledSlots, int totalSlots, int filledCampCommSlots, int campCommSlots, String description, String staffID, String visibility)
      Constructs a Camp object with the given attributes.
      Parameters:
      campID - The unique identifier for the camp.
      campName - The name of the camp.
      dates - The dates of the camp in the format "DD-MM-YY,DD-MM-YY".
      registrationClosingDate - The closing date for camp registration.
      openTo - The faculty to which the camp is open.
      location - The location of the camp.
      filledSlots - The number of attendees that have joined the camp.
      totalSlots - The total number of attendees that can join the camp.
      filledCampCommSlots - The number of committee members that have joined the camp.
      campCommSlots - The total committee slots, defaulting to 10.
      description - The description of the camp.
      staffID - The staff ID associated with the camp.
      visibility - The visibility status of the camp.
